## Educational Usage Guidelines

### For Students
- Use the material as a complement to formal learning
- Practice exercises in order of difficulty
- Consult notes to understand theoretical concepts
- Visualize flowcharts to understand algorithms
- Test different resolution approaches

### For Teachers
- Use the material as a reference for classes
- Adapt exercises as necessary
- Use flowcharts to explain concepts
- Apply methodologies in the classroom
- Contribute with improvements and new exercises

### For Contributors
- Maintain educational focus
- Follow established standards
- Document contributions adequately
- Test code before submitting
- Respect different knowledge levels